9) Core Flows

A) Receive/Scan
- Input: {barcode|manual}, name/sku, qty/unit, lot/expiry, location, cost (optional)
- Output: labels (PDF), batchId
- Events: inventory.received → optional savings calc

B) Use/Decrement (from Meals/Batch)
- Input: selected recipes/batch → computeDeltaFromRecipes
- Preview: human table; FEFO picks; conflicts (insufficient qty)
- Apply: applyDelta → patchId; Undo supported
- Events: inventory.updated

C) Garden Harvest
- Input: harvest entry → produce[]
- Location assign (Root Cellar/Fridge); “Confirm moved” logs timestamp
- Events: harvest.logged, savings.updated

D) Preservation
- Method + items → derived SKUs (e.g., TOMATO_FRESH → TOMATO_SAUCE_QT)
- Labels (date/method/lot/reheat if cooked)
- Events: preservation.logged, inventory.updated

E) **Animals Intake → Processing → Butchery**
1) Intake: AnimalsIntakeForm → AnimalsStore
   - Emit animals.registered; planProcessing → events guarded by Hebrew calendar; emit animals.processing.scheduled
2) Cut Sheet: Upload/Fill → ButcheryCutSheetMapper
   - Emit butchery.cut_sheet.created; map rows → SKUs; compute yields (live→carcass→retail)
3) Cooling/Compliance: CoolingTracker logs temps; alert if slow-chill; location “Chill Room”
   - Emit butchery.carcass.chilled; propose move to Freezer when ok
4) Packaging & Labels: buildPackagingRun → labelAgent.buildButcheryLabels → print; Location moves
   - applyDelta(produce+move+consume materials) → patchId; emit butchery.packaging.run.completed + butchery.completed
5) Analytics: Savings ledger uses local price benchmarks; add yield cards to Overview

F) **Animal Shares/Orders (Cut-Sheet Linked)**
- Open Offer: select **animalIds** (required) and **cutSheetIds** (if available); pooling OFF by default.
- Reserve: create order; copy linkage; capture deposit & contract.
- Allocate: ShareAllocator shows **eligiblePackages(offerId)**; enforces linkage; outputs move[] to “Reserved/<BuyerId>”; prints buyer labels & packing slips.
- Bill: priceQuote (live/hanging/retail); invoice; record payments (QuickBooks stub).
- Pickup: schedule (Hebrew guard); reminders; scan-out from Reserved; mark fulfilled.
- Shortfall/Surplus: show delta by animal; substitutions within same animal first; pooling requires buyer consent & admin toggle.

G) Lists & Purchasing (Unified)
- Inputs: lowStock (below par), planDelta (meals/batches), butchery materials (bags/casings)
- Output: grouped list by store/aisle; export PDF/SMS/email; calendar sync with Hebrew guard
- Events: lists.generated

10) Scanning & Labeling
- Barcode: QuaggaJS/HID; manual SKU picker fallback
- SKU mapping: JSON/db; alias search
- Labels: buildFoodLabels, buildButcheryLabels, **buildBuyerLabels (shows buyer/animal/cut-sheet)**

11) Alerts & Rotation
- Low Stock (par), Expiring (FEFO), Spoilage logs
- **Chill/Temp** alerts; block freezer move until safe

